description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Rotherham NHS Foundation Trust&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Pharmacy Department &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Pharmacy Senior ACT Technician&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Salary Scale: A4C Band 5&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Full Time: 37.5 hours&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Wanted&lt;/strong&gt;:  Hard working, enthusiastic team player with a positive attitude.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Reward:&lt;/strong&gt;  Working within a friendly, motivated forward thinking team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Rotherham NHS Foundation Trust is looking for an exceptional ACT pharmacy technician to play an integral part within our dispensary services.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Rotherham NHS Foundation Trust is a combined Acute and Community Trust serving a population of over 260,000 with over 4,500 staff and income in excess of £250 million.  Our vision is to be an outstanding Trust, delivering excellent care at home, in our community and in hospital.  We will achieve this by working with patients, the public and partners to make a positive difference to the health and wellbeing of the people of Rotherham.  We are working successfully with partners across South Yorkshire and Bassetlaw as part of the Integrated Care System, where we are leading and collaborating in several key work streams and service areas.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We set high standards for the services that we deliver.  We aim to be an outstanding Trust and we are enthusiastic about delivering excellent health care for our patients.  We have high expectations of ourselves and others.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We value the importance of working together with patients, carers and families to ensure we provide high quality patient centred care.  We are committed to working with partners and stakeholders across Rotherham, South Yorkshire, and Bassetlaw to develop sustainable services for the population we serve.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;It is essential that the post holder has an NVQ 3 in pharmaceutical science or equivalent and a minimum of twelve months’ post experience, with an accredited checking qualification and registered with the GPhC.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will work 37.5 hours per week including late night, weekends and Bank Holidays.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Estimated interview date will be 19/11/2020&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;For informal enquiries please contact:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Kieren Bradshaw (Pharmacy Business Manager) :  kieren.bradshaw@nhs.net or 01709 428099&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Philip Clarkson ( Lead Technician Dispensary Philip.clarkson1@nhs.net or 01709 427824 &lt;/p&gt;
